1
00:41:00,327 --> 00:41:04,161
<i>The humanoids must first be destroyed.</i>
必须首先消灭这些人类

2
00:41:04,807 --> 00:41:09,437
<i>You will re-enter cells</i>
<i>to conserve energy.</i>
为了节省能力， 你们得重新进入格子间

3
00:41:09,687 --> 00:41:11,006
Keep back!
后退！

4
00:41:11,807 --> 00:41:13,126
Your gun.
你的枪

5
00:41:17,907 --> 00:41:20,298
You've killed him, you murderer.
你杀了他，你这个杀人犯

6
00:41:20,367 --> 00:41:23,535
- No. He is fortunate. I spared him.
- You mean you missed him.
- 不。他很幸运。我饶了他  - 你是说你没打中吧

7
00:41:23,607 --> 00:41:25,779
Silence! I could have destroyed him
if I wanted to.
闭嘴！我本可以杀了他的，如果我想的话

8
00:41:25,867 --> 00:41:28,825
- Shall I kill them now?
- No, that will not be necessary.
- 我现在该杀了他们吗？  - 不, 并没有必要

9
00:41:28,907 --> 00:41:30,898
I'm sure the Cybermen
will have a use for them.
我能肯定，赛博人能好好利用他们

10
00:41:32,067 --> 00:41:35,264
You will make excellent
experimental specimens.
你们将成为绝佳的实验样品

11
00:41:35,427 --> 00:41:37,736
Oh, let me help him, please!
噢, 让我帮他一下, 拜托！

12
00:41:38,387 --> 00:41:39,706
No tricks.
别耍花招

13
00:41:39,787 --> 00:41:42,176
Still think you can bargain with the Cybermen?
还觉得你可以跟赛博人谈条件？

14
00:41:42,267 --> 00:41:44,417
Certainly. This time on our terms.
当然, 这次得按我们的条件来

15
00:41:52,547 --> 00:41:54,981
I wish to speak to the Controller.
我要同管理员谈话

16
00:41:56,467 --> 00:41:59,265
I wish to speak to the Controller!
我要同管理员谈话

17
00:42:06,107 --> 00:42:09,065
<i>He is now prepared.</i>
现在他已经准备好了

18
00:42:09,867 --> 00:42:11,903
<i>Release him.</i>
放把出去吧

19
00:42:21,647 --> 00:42:23,126
They're coming.
他们来了

20
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:27,723
Now, gentlemen, you will see how
I shall use the power of the Cybermen.
现在, 先生们, 你们将会见识到我是如何利用赛博人的力量的

21
00:42:27,807 --> 00:42:30,799
Use, maybe, but you'll never
control the Cybermen.
利用, 有可能; 但你永远别想控制住赛博人

22
00:42:30,967 --> 00:42:32,844
- Behind you.  - Stop!
- 在你后面  - 停下！

23
00:42:33,367 --> 00:42:35,562
You know what this can do to you.
你知道这个会把你怎么样

24
00:42:39,367 --> 00:42:42,006
Toberman, it is good that you are back.
Toberman, 你回来真是太好了

25
00:42:42,767 --> 00:42:44,086
Watch them.
看着他们

26
00:42:47,687 --> 00:42:50,884
- Doctor, he seems er...
- Yes, Jamie, yes.
- 博士, 他似乎...  - 是的, Jamie, 是的

27
00:42:51,287 --> 00:42:53,778
I shall let you be revitalised, to survive.
我该让你充电了, 否则活不下去了

28
00:42:53,867 --> 00:42:55,244
It must be now.
现在就得

29
00:42:59,367 --> 00:43:01,676
Come forward. Slowly.
往前面来, 慢慢地

30
00:43:01,767 --> 00:43:03,405
- Be careful.  - Leave this to me.
- 小心点  - 把这交给我吧

31
00:43:14,907 --> 00:43:17,626
You are absolutely crazy to trust them!
你觉得是疯了, 居然相信他们！

32
00:43:17,707 --> 00:43:19,026
You think so?
你这么觉得？

33
00:43:19,107 --> 00:43:23,225
Then perhaps you and your colleagues
had better join him. Go on. Go on!
也许你和你的同事们最好跟他去, 走, 走！

34
00:43:25,187 --> 00:43:27,223
- The girl stays with us.  - No!
- 这女孩留在我们这里  - 不！

35
00:43:27,307 --> 00:43:28,706
She is our hostage.
他是我们的人质

36
00:43:33,227 --> 00:43:34,819
Close the hatch.
关上舱门

37
00:43:36,907 --> 00:43:38,818
You seem to be in trouble.
你看来有麻烦了

38
00:43:40,147 --> 00:43:42,661
<i>The energy...</i>
能量

39
00:43:42,747 --> 00:43:45,580
<i>levels...are...low.</i>
水平...低

40
00:43:46,067 --> 00:43:49,616
<i>We...will...survive.</i>
我们...得...活下去

41
00:43:49,707 --> 00:43:53,382
<i>You will help us.</i>
你得帮助我们

42
00:43:53,667 --> 00:43:57,182
<i>You will...help...us...</i>
你得...帮助...我们

43
00:43:57,347 --> 00:43:59,019
Yes. Yes, certainly.
是的, 是的, 当然了

44
00:43:59,107 --> 00:44:02,622
- Jamie, Professor.
- You don't mean to say you're going to help them?
- Jamie, 教授  - 你不是想说你打算帮助他们吧？

45
00:44:02,707 --> 00:44:04,902
Surely not. You can't support these creatures!
当然不能. 你不能帮这些怪物啊！

46
00:44:04,987 --> 00:44:06,864
I think it best. Come on.
我已经想好了, 来吧

47
00:44:07,027 --> 00:44:08,346
Come along.
过来

48
00:44:08,427 --> 00:44:09,746
That's it.
就这样

49
00:44:14,467 --> 00:44:19,700
<i>Do...you...understand...the...machine?</i>
你...能...搞懂...那个...机器吗？

50
00:44:19,787 --> 00:44:21,300
Yes. One moment.
是的, 等一下

51
00:44:21,387 --> 00:44:24,584
Have you taken leave of your senses?
Let's help Victoria.
你丧失判断力了吗？我们来帮 Victoria

52
00:44:24,667 --> 00:44:26,339
In a moment, Jamie.
等一下, Jamie

53
00:44:27,707 --> 00:44:29,504
(DOCTOR) Now, are you ready?
现在， 你准备好了吗？

54
00:44:38,907 --> 00:44:42,104
<i>We will survive.</i>
我们会活下去

55
00:44:42,187 --> 00:44:44,178
<i>We will sur...</i>
我们会活...

56
00:44:44,647 --> 00:44:47,817
Now, where would you rather
have him - in or out of there?
现在, 你是愿意他待在里面呢, 还是外面？

57
00:44:48,207 --> 00:44:50,801
Oh, I see what you mean.
哦, 我明白你的意思了

58
00:44:50,887 --> 00:44:53,845
Only we must make sure
that he stays in there.
只是我们必须得确保他会待在里面

59
00:44:56,187 --> 00:44:59,782
Do you really believe you can bargain
with those terrible Cybermen?
你真的相信你可以同那些可怕的赛博人讲条件？

60
00:45:00,167 --> 00:45:02,427
That is our concern, not yours.
这是我们的事情, 不关你事

61
00:45:02,507 --> 00:45:04,384
I'm talking to him, not you.
我在跟他说话, 不是你

62
00:45:04,447 --> 00:45:06,922
They will have to agree to our plan.
他们将不得不同意我们的计划

63
00:45:08,107 --> 00:45:09,859
Told you we shouldn't have touched it.
跟你说过我们本不该动它的

64
00:45:09,947 --> 00:45:12,063
Yes. Turn it off. It's out of control.
是的。关掉它, 失控了

65
00:45:13,107 --> 00:45:15,496
(NOISE DIES DOWN)

66
00:45:21,187 --> 00:45:22,700
It's taken over.
被他们接管了？

67
00:45:22,787 --> 00:45:24,106
I think not.
我觉得没有

68
00:45:24,187 --> 00:45:27,736
There must be some sort
of internal timing mechanism.
肯定有某种内部计时机制

69
00:45:27,827 --> 00:45:30,739
Jamie, I hope you made
those ropes secure.
Jamie，我期望你把绳子绑牢了

70
00:45:30,827 --> 00:45:33,705
The King of Beasties himself
couldnae get out of that?
那个怪兽之王不能自己跑出来吧？

71
00:45:41,347 --> 00:45:45,535
Jamie, remind me to give you
a lesson in tying knots some time.
Jamie, 回头提醒我找个时间教你如何打结

72
00:45:45,707 --> 00:45:47,618
What do you hope to gain from this?
你想通过这个达到什么目的？

73
00:45:47,787 --> 00:45:50,665
- That does not concern you.
- They might as well know.
- 那不关你事  - 他们可能也知道

74
00:45:50,747 --> 00:45:53,545
We are going to build a better world.
我们要建造一个更好的世界

75
00:45:53,627 --> 00:45:55,538
(CALLUM) Better? But who for?
更好？对谁更好？

76
00:45:57,227 --> 00:45:59,183
I told you to watch the door.
我让你看好门的

77
00:45:59,347 --> 00:46:00,700
Aagh!
啊！

78
00:46:00,867 --> 00:46:02,186
Aagh!
啊！

79
00:46:03,587 --> 00:46:04,906
Toberman.
Toberman.﻿

80
00:46:05,867 --> 00:46:07,186
Victoria.
Victoria.﻿

81
00:46:12,827 --> 00:46:16,137
- <i>You have done well.</i>  - Toberman!
- 你做得很好  - Toberman!

82
00:46:16,227 --> 00:46:17,660
<i>Silence.</i>
安静

83
00:46:17,747 --> 00:46:21,581
<i>He is now under our control.</i>
他现在处于我们控制之下了

84
00:46:21,667 --> 00:46:24,181
<i>Open the tombs.</i>
打开墓室

85
00:46:24,267 --> 00:46:25,586
No.
不

86
00:46:28,267 --> 00:46:30,098
You have broken your promise.
你已经打破你的诺言了

87
00:46:30,267 --> 00:46:33,339
<i>Cybermen do not promise.</i>
赛博人不做承诺

88
00:46:33,867 --> 00:46:37,098
<i>Such ideas have no value.</i>
这样的观念没有价值

89
00:46:37,667 --> 00:46:38,986
<i>Open.</i>
打开

90
00:46:40,107 --> 00:46:41,426
No.
不

91
00:47:01,747 --> 00:47:04,261
<i>That gun will not harm me.</i>
那把枪伤害不了我

92
00:47:07,667 --> 00:47:09,146
Aagh!
啊！

93
00:47:18,627 --> 00:47:20,424
Look what they've done.
看看他们干了啥

94
00:47:20,507 --> 00:47:23,977
You are not like them. You're a man
like us. You must help us.
你跟他们不一样, 你是我们的一员, 你必须帮助我们

95
00:47:25,107 --> 00:47:27,905
He has killed Kaftan.
You must help us.
他已经杀了 Kaftan, 你必须帮助我们

96
00:47:29,227 --> 00:47:33,186
<i>You will report to the surface.</i>
你得向地面报告情况

97
00:47:56,187 --> 00:47:59,145
(UNINTELLIGIBLE NOISES)

98
00:48:06,907 --> 00:48:08,499
Jamie, the hatch!
Jamie, 舱门！

99
00:48:10,827 --> 00:48:12,226
The gun, Jamie!
枪, Jamie!

100
00:48:31,827 --> 00:48:33,499
There's another one, Doctor!
这里还有一个，博士！

101
00:48:35,467 --> 00:48:37,776
(CRASHING)

102
00:48:38,947 --> 00:48:40,380
Are there any more?
还有吗？

103
00:48:40,467 --> 00:48:42,458
No. It's gone quiet.
I'll close the hatch.
没了, 安静下来了。我去关上舱门

104
00:48:42,547 --> 00:48:45,107
Wait a minute.
We'd better go down there.
等一下, 我们最好下去

105
00:48:45,187 --> 00:48:47,655
- Oh, no, not again!
- It's the only way to make sure.
- 噢不，别再下去了！  - 只有这样才能确认

106
00:48:47,747 --> 00:48:50,625
- I'll go with you.
- No. You stay and look after Victoria.
- 我跟你一起去  - 不, 你留在这里照看 Victoria

107
00:48:51,227 --> 00:48:53,104
I'll take somebody else.
我另外带个人去

108
00:48:57,267 --> 00:48:58,859
Toberman.
Toberman﻿

109
00:48:58,947 --> 00:49:01,620
You see what these creatures
have done to you?
你看到这些怪物对你做了什么吧？

110
00:49:01,707 --> 00:49:05,985
They've tried to make you like them.
Do you understand?
他们想把你变得跟他们一样, 你明白吗？

111
00:49:06,627 --> 00:49:09,903
They've tried to make you their slave.
They just want to use you.
他们试图把你变成他们的奴隶．他们想利用你

112
00:49:09,987 --> 00:49:13,582
They are evil. Think of Kaftan.
他们是邪恶的, 想想 Kaftan

113
00:49:13,747 --> 00:49:16,944
- Evil!
- They must be destroyed, you see?
- 邪恶！  - 必须摧毁他们, 你明白吗？

114
00:49:17,027 --> 00:49:18,938
Evil must be destroyed.
邪恶必须被摧毁

115
00:49:19,027 --> 00:49:20,619
Now, come.
现在, 来吧

116
00:49:20,707 --> 00:49:22,026
Destroyed!
摧毁！

117
00:49:23,067 --> 00:49:24,420
Come on.
快来

118
00:49:25,507 --> 00:49:26,826
Come on!
快来！

119
00:49:35,587 --> 00:49:37,179
- Good luck.  - Thank you.
- 祝你好运  - 谢谢你

120
00:49:37,267 --> 00:49:39,576
- Doctor, the gun.
- I shan't need that.
- 博士, 枪   - 我应该不需要那个

121
00:49:40,587 --> 00:49:42,179
Should have taken it.
你应该带着

122
00:49:42,347 --> 00:49:45,100
- Aagh!
- Poor Mr Callum. How are you feeling?
- 啊！  - 可怜的 Callum. 你觉得怎么样？

123
00:49:45,187 --> 00:49:46,939
I can't move my arm.
我动不了我的胳膊了

124
00:50:00,187 --> 00:50:01,939
Move quietly.
慢慢移动

125
00:50:02,027 --> 00:50:03,858
They're all dormant, see?
他们都休眠了, 看？

126
00:50:09,547 --> 00:50:10,866
Evil!
邪恶

127
00:50:11,027 --> 00:50:14,542
No! Quietly. They're only asleep.
不！安静点, 他们只是睡着了

128
00:50:14,627 --> 00:50:18,461
They're not frozen yet.
You watch them. I have things to do.
还没有被冻住．你看着他们, 我还有事要做

129
00:50:19,387 --> 00:50:20,979
Now, let me see.
现在, 让我看看

130
00:50:21,707 --> 00:50:23,026
Yes.
是了

131
00:50:25,187 --> 00:50:27,542
The cryostat! You're freezing them!
低温保持器！你要冻死他们啊! 

132
00:50:28,027 --> 00:50:29,346
Klieg!
Klieg!﻿

133
00:50:34,387 --> 00:50:36,503
No! You'll wake them up!
不！你会唤醒他们的！

134
00:50:36,587 --> 00:50:38,623
That is exactly my intention.
那正是我的目的

135
00:50:38,707 --> 00:50:40,982
You still don't understand, do you?
你还是没明白, 是吗？

136
00:50:41,147 --> 00:50:42,944
Their Controller is dead.
他们的管理员已经死了

137
00:50:43,027 --> 00:50:46,656
Now I shall control them.
They will do what I say.
现在我来控制他们, 我说什么他们就做什么

138
00:50:47,227 --> 00:50:48,546
You see, Doctor.
你看, 博士

139
00:50:48,707 --> 00:50:50,563
Yours is the privilege to witness...
你获得了特权, 来见证...

140
00:50:50,647 --> 00:50:56,745
...for the first time the union between
mass power and my absolute intelligence.
...超级力量和我绝对智慧的第一次融合

141
00:50:58,107 --> 00:50:59,665
Who is that?
谁?

142
00:51:00,787 --> 00:51:02,186
Come out.
出来

143
00:51:04,587 --> 00:51:06,896
Come out or I shall kill this man!
出来, 否则我就杀了这个人！

144
00:51:10,267 --> 00:51:11,666
Oh, it's you.
噢, 是你

145
00:51:12,667 --> 00:51:14,862
Go to that wall, all of you.
到墙那里去, 你们全部

146
00:51:15,747 --> 00:51:17,146
All of you!
你们全部过去！

147
00:51:25,187 --> 00:51:26,506
No.
不

148
00:51:27,387 --> 00:51:31,266
I have a better idea, a much better idea.
我有一个好主意, 一个非常好的主意

149
00:51:31,347 --> 00:51:33,861
I shall leave you to the Cybermen.
我要把你们留给赛博人

150
00:51:34,707 --> 00:51:36,982
I'm sure they'll have some use for you.
我肯定他们拿你们有用

151
00:51:37,467 --> 00:51:39,185
Or parts of you!
或者拿你的部件来用！

152
00:51:45,707 --> 00:51:47,584
(KLIEG SCREAMS)

153
00:52:02,587 --> 00:52:05,385
Quick, Jamie! These two levers together.
快, Jamie! 这两根杆一起拉

154
00:52:06,147 --> 00:52:09,264
- I can't shift this one.
- What? You've got to trip that first.
- 我拉不动这个  - 什么？你必须得先按那个

155
00:52:57,307 --> 00:53:00,697
Last time they were frozen
for five centuries.
上一次他们冰冻了五个世纪

156
00:53:01,507 --> 00:53:03,384
This time it must be forever.
这一次必须得是永远

157
00:53:29,787 --> 00:53:31,459
Oh, Doctor!
噢, 博士！

158
00:53:31,547 --> 00:53:34,744
Here we are, Victoria, safe and sound.
Close the hatch.
我们上来了, Victoria, 安然无恙．关上舱门

159
00:53:43,027 --> 00:53:44,506
There we are.
差不多了

160
00:53:46,547 --> 00:53:47,946
Now then.
还有

161
00:53:50,707 --> 00:53:54,336
The best thing about a machine
that makes sense -
一个机器最好的地方是...

162
00:53:55,107 --> 00:53:58,543
you can very easily
make it turn out nonsense.
你可以很容易地把它变成废物

163
00:54:00,587 --> 00:54:03,943
- Now I think you'd better all go outside.
- What are you going to do, Doctor?
- 现在我觉得你们最好都出去  - 你打算干什么，博士？

164
00:54:04,027 --> 00:54:06,495
I'm going to re-electrify the main doors.
我要让主门重新上电

165
00:54:06,587 --> 00:54:10,421
Only this time I'm going to include
the hatch and the control panel.
只不过这次要包含舱门和控制面板

166
00:54:10,507 --> 00:54:13,738
Anyone touching any of them
will get a considerable shock.
任何人碰里面的一个, 都会被电到休克

167
00:54:13,827 --> 00:54:16,466
A fatal one. Now, everyone outside.
很致命的．现在, 所有人都出去

168
00:54:17,307 --> 00:54:21,016
Please take him with you.
I shall be glad to see him outside.
请把他带上跟你一起．我乐意见到他在外面

169
00:54:24,857 --> 00:54:27,087
There we are. That's done.
好了, 完成了

170
00:54:27,817 --> 00:54:31,810
We just have to close the main doors
and the circuit is complete.
我们只要关上主门, 电路就接通了

171
00:54:31,897 --> 00:54:33,808
Thank goodness for that.
感谢上帝

172
00:54:36,497 --> 00:54:37,816
Doctor.
博士

173
00:54:38,057 --> 00:54:39,410
Doctor!
博士！

174
00:54:42,217 --> 00:54:43,570
Jamie...
Jamie...﻿

175
00:54:44,537 --> 00:54:46,892
You go that way. I'll go this way.
你去那边, 我走这边

176
00:54:47,337 --> 00:54:49,373
That gives us more of a chance.
这样胜算大些

177
00:54:49,457 --> 00:54:52,096
When I say run, run.
